@wchan, downgrading to 0.1.1 works!!! Thanks a lot.
@gillhofer, Arch linux 4.3.3 with CUDA 7.0, gcc/g++ 4.9.3 and bazel 0.1.1 works. You can give it a try. Btw, I have nvidia gtx 660, so setting compute capability to 3.0 with
$ TF_UNOFFICIAL_SETTING=1 ./configure is needed.

body:
@wchan, downgrading to 0.1.1 works!!! Thanks a lot.

@gillhofer, Arch linux 4.3.3 with CUDA 7.0, gcc/g++ 4.9.3 and bazel 0.1.1 works. You can give it a try. Btw, I have nvidia gtx 660, so setting compute capability to 3.0 with
`$ TF_UNOFFICIAL_SETTING=1 ./configure` is needed.
